org.whispercomm.c2dm4j
Enum ResponseType

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<ResponseType>
      org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.ResponseType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<ResponseType>
public enum ResponseType
extends Enum<ResponseType>

An enum representing the response from the C2DM service for a message push request. The class encapsulating the response can be retrieved via the associatedClass() method.

Descriptions for the individual enum values are taken from the C2DM web page.

Author:
David R. Bild

Enum Constant Detail

Success

public static final ResponseType Success
Message was successfully received by the C2DM service. N.B., this does not indicate the message has been delivered to the client yet.

ServiceUnavailable

public static final ResponseType ServiceUnavailable
Indicates that the server is temporarily unavailable (i.e., because of timeouts, etc). Sender must retry later, honoring any Retry-After header included in the response. Application servers must implement the exponential back off. Senders that create problems risk being blacklisted.

Unauthorized

public static final ResponseType Unauthorized
Indicates that the ClientLogin AUTH_TOKEN used to validate the sender is invalid.

QuotaExceeded

public static final ResponseType QuotaExceeded
Too many messages sent by the sender. Retry after a while.

DeviceQuotaExceeded

public static final ResponseType DeviceQuotaExceeded
Too many messages sent by the sender to a specific device. Retry after a while.

MissingRegistration

public static final ResponseType MissingRegistration
Missing registration_id. Sender should always add the registration_id to the request.

InvalidRegistration

public static final ResponseType InvalidRegistration
Bad registration_id. Sender should remove this registration_id.

MismatchSenderId

public static final ResponseType MismatchSenderId
The sender_id contained in the registration_id does not match the sender id used to register with the C2DM servers.

NotRegistered

public static final ResponseType NotRegistered
The user has uninstalled the application or turned off notifications. Sender should stop sending messages to this device and delete the registration_id. The client needs to re-register with the C2DM servers to receive notifications again.

MessageTooBig

public static final ResponseType MessageTooBig
The payload of the message is too big, see the limitations. Reduce the size of the message.

MissingCollapseKey

public static final ResponseType MissingCollapseKey
Collapse key is required. Include the collapse key in the request.
